{"title_page": "The Enemy Within (Kennedy book)", "text_new": "{{italic title}}\n{{Infobox book\n| italic title   = <!--(see above)-->\n| name           = The Enemy Within\n| image          = \n| image_size     = \n| alt            = \n| caption        = \n| author         = [[Robert F. Kennedy]]\n| audio_read_by  = \n| title_orig     = \n| orig_lang_code = \n| title_working  = \n| translator     = \n| illustrator    = \n| cover_artist   = \n| country        = \n| language       = English\n| series         = \n| release_number = \n| subject        = \n| genre          = Non-fiction\n| set_in         = \n| publisher      = \n| publisher2     = \n| pub_date       = \n| english_pub_date = \n| published      = 1960\n| media_type     = \n| pages          = \n| awards         = \n| isbn           = \n| isbn_note      = \n| oclc           = \n| dewey          = \n| congress       = \n| preceded_by    = \n| followed_by    = \n| native_wikisource = \n| wikisource     = \n| notes          =\n| exclude_cover  = \n| website        =\n}}\n\n'''''The Enemy Within: The McClellan Committee's Crusade Against Jimmy Hoffa and Corrupt Labor Unions''''' is a book by [[Robert F. Kennedy]]<ref name=spart>{{cite web|title=Robert F. Kennedy|url=http://spartacus-educational.com/USAkennedyR.htm|accessdate=18 November 2015}}</ref> (assisted by [[John Seigenthaler]])<ref>{{cite book |last1=Hilty |first1=James |title=Robert Kennedy: Brother Protector |date=2000 |publisher=Temple University Press |isbn=978-1-56639-766-7 |page=609 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_QpECR5E7_0C&pg=PA609 |language=en}}</ref> first published in 1960, and republished in 1994.<ref name=tew>{{cite web|title=The Enemy Within: The McClellan Committee's Crusade Against Jimmy Hoffa And Corrupt Labor Unions by Robert F. Kennedy \u2014 Reviews, Discussion, Bookclubs, Lists|url=http://www.goodreads.com/book/show/313839.The_Enemy_Within|accessdate=18 November 2015}}</ref>  [[Edwin Guthman]], chairman of the Robert F. Kennedy Memorial provided the introduction to the 1994 edition.<ref name=tew/>\n\nThe work details events and information uncovered between 1956 and 1959 by the [[United States Senate Select Committee on Improper Activities in Labor and Management]] in which Kennedy served as chief counsel. As Robert Kennedy was intimately involved, the book is somewhat autobiographical.\n\nRobert Kennedy describes the [[International Brotherhood of Teamsters|Teamsters Union]] as the most powerful institution in the United States aside the [[Federal government of the United States|United States Government]] itself (1994, p. 161). According to Robert Kennedy, [[George Meany]], former president of the [[AFL\u2013CIO|AFL-CIO]], has called [[Jimmy Hoffa]] organized labor's No. 1 Enemy (1994, p. 161).\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Robert F. Kennedy}}\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Enemy Within}}\n[[Category:Works by Robert F. Kennedy]]\n[[Category:Robert F. Kennedy]]\n[[Category:Political books]]\n[[Category:Trade unions]]\n[[Category:1960 non-fiction books]]\n{{US-poli-book-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{italic title}}\n{{Infobox book\n| italic title   = <!--(see above)-->\n| name           = The Enemy Within\n| image          = \n| image_size     = \n| alt            = \n| caption        = \n| author         = [[Robert F. Kennedy]]\n| audio_read_by  = \n| title_orig     = \n| orig_lang_code = \n| title_working  = \n| translator     = \n| illustrator    = \n| cover_artist   = \n| country        = \n| language       = English\n| series         = \n| release_number = \n| subject        = \n| genre          = Non-fiction\n| set_in         = \n| publisher      = \n| publisher2     = \n| pub_date       = \n| english_pub_date = \n| published      = 1960\n| media_type     = \n| pages          = \n| awards         = \n| isbn           = \n| isbn_note      = \n| oclc           = \n| dewey          = \n| congress       = \n| preceded_by    = \n| followed_by    = \n| native_wikisource = \n| wikisource     = \n| notes          =\n| exclude_cover  = \n| website        =\n}}\n\n'''''The Enemy Within: The McClellan Committee's Crusade Against Jimmy Hoffa and Corrupt Labor Unions''''' is a book by [[Robert F. Kennedy]]<ref name=spart>{{cite web|title=Robert F. Kennedy|url=http://spartacus-educational.com/USAkennedyR.htm|accessdate=18 November 2015}}</ref> (assisted by [[John Seigenthaler]])</ref><ref>{{cite book |last1=Hilty |first1=James |title=Robert Kennedy: Brother Protector |date=2000 |publisher=Temple University Press |isbn=978-1-56639-766-7 |page=609 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_QpECR5E7_0C&pg=PA609 |language=en}}</ref> first published in 1960, and republished in 1994.<ref name=tew>{{cite web|title=The Enemy Within: The McClellan Committee's Crusade Against Jimmy Hoffa And Corrupt Labor Unions by Robert F. Kennedy \u2014 Reviews, Discussion, Bookclubs, Lists|url=http://www.goodreads.com/book/show/313839.The_Enemy_Within|accessdate=18 November 2015}}</ref>  [[Edwin Guthman]], chairman of the Robert F. Kennedy Memorial provided the introduction to the 1994 edition.<ref name=tew/>\n\nThe work details events and information uncovered between 1956 and 1959 by the [[United States Senate Select Committee on Improper Activities in Labor and Management]] in which Kennedy served as chief counsel. As Robert Kennedy was intimately involved, the book is somewhat autobiographical.\n\nRobert Kennedy describes the [[International Brotherhood of Teamsters|Teamsters Union]] as the most powerful institution in the United States aside the [[Federal government of the United States|United States Government]] itself (1994, p. 161). According to Robert Kennedy, [[George Meany]], former president of the [[AFL\u2013CIO|AFL-CIO]], has called [[Jimmy Hoffa]] organized labor's No. 1 Enemy (1994, p. 161).\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Robert F. Kennedy}}\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Enemy Within}}\n[[Category:Works by Robert F. Kennedy]]\n[[Category:Robert 